{
  "texts": [
    "Additionally, the development of a robust control system often requires a detailed understanding of system dynamics.",
    "Building modeling can provide dynamic feedback to test various control algorithms, which will be discussed in more detail in the next section.",
    "Fault detection also plays a crucial part in reducing maintenance costs and increasing the energy efficiency of building operations (Dong et al., 2014).",
    "However, faults in an actual building do not occur frequently, and it is hard to collect fault data for analysis.",
    "Data sets for fault diagnosis are usually created through testbed experiments or simulations."
  ]
}